    "href": "#fn-1",
    "className": "footnote-ref"
  }, "1")), " for example."), mdx("p", null, "Still searching for its place in the scientific field, Museology seeks\nto resolve some metamuseological issues, as defined by Str\xE1nsk\xFD, in a\nreflexive perspective that involves museum theory and practice. This\nsearch also involves the definition of a methodology and a terminology,\nor yet, the adoption of ", mdx("em", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "epistemic agreements"), " to solve a lack of\nconsensus caused, in most part, by language differences. We can see\nthose efforts in publications like Key Concepts", mdx("sup", {
    parentName: "p",
    "id": "fnref-2"
  }, mdx("a", {
    parentName: "sup",
    "href": "#fn-2",
    "className": "footnote-ref"
  }, "2")), ", the dictionary", mdx("sup", {
